@ScottFlashheart @ArtholeThom I hear this! I got the same when I recently looked for meds. I was so pissed off -maybe I wouldn’t be so exhausted if I didn’t have to mask my symptoms so I can cope! There is a huge issue with gate keeping and prescribers. Ask if you want to try them. You won’t know until you do

@ScottFlashheart @ArtholeThom Aren’t helpful as we forget to use them! CBT therapy etc can sometimes provide a bit of relief. Communication with managers/family/loved ones really helps so knowing your symptoms to inform people when struggling is a huge help.  But meds can be great for actual brain silence!

@ScottFlashheart @ArtholeThom Hahahaha Oh god where to start. Stimulants work really well for some but not everyone (me included) so I have medical cannabis instead. I’m still new to it but it’s been the best thing so far to combat my hyperactivity / hyper focus. Apps/diaries/planners can work but often-
